flowRoot.flowPara: Single Nucleotide Variants (SNVs) must be a table with three columns: first column contains gene symbols, second column specifies the type of variant (among Frame_Shift_Del, Frame_Shift_Ins, In_Frame_Del, In_Frame_Ins, Missense_Mutation, Nonsense_Mutation, Silent, Splice_Site, Translation_Start_Site, Nonstop_Mutation, RNA, Targeted_Region, as defined by MAF file specification “Variant Classification” field).The third column consists of the amino acid change (e.g. T790M).
